content: I studied all through this app and even got 90s on practice. But the actual exam was so different that I feel this prepware is not helpful nomore

Missing a lot of questions. I took my FAA PowerPlant written Jan of 2021, and I'd say PrepWare only covered about 60-70% of the questions I was given. A lot of the existing questions had been reworded, but those are easy enough. Most of the questions not covered by this app can be figured out if you know the system, however the FAA written likes to ask specific and annoying questions that the only practical way of knowing is just memorizing. Which is a big disappoinment that they aren't covered.
The app is nice and easy, but I wish in the test mode all the answers are highlighted so is will be very easy to read

This is the worst of the three apps. I know i maybe anal and oddly complaining about 96% but here are my reasons. ASA is not being public about the fact that they have no clue on the FAA updates. These tests are CLOSED and are no longer public knowledge, so your basically on your own when it comes time to test. My intent here is to let everyone know so your not supprised. I encountered 7 new never seen questions on my 101 question test (yes some are more than 100 questions) so thats a 7% miss by prepware.  there maybe possibly more, since i got 7 new ques out of 101  what is the real number of new questions in the entire 1000 question bank, 70 new questions? on all 3 tests i figure I came across a total of 15 new questions.I went to a good 147 school and some of these new faa  ques were stupid and worthless to memorize,so now we have to memorize the faa-8083s and such,wow stupid. I called ASA and talked to their update guy and he pretty much agreed the tests are now a mystery. I could score 100 on my prepware all day long but when I was never told these are somewhat outdated questions.all this said  this " IS"  a bargain at 5 bucks and you will get a passing score with these apps
